args:
The prince secures a pact with Zodiark—who
now hosts his father's soul—but Zethia is lost
and her double defeated. Now in possession of
Zethia's body, the Other claims that she is
the new empress.
I am he, yet I am not. I am Zodiark,\nthe Shadowwyrm.
I am he who waltzes in the black...\nI am darkness incarnate... And I am\nsoul-fused with your fallen father!
From this moment on, I will be your\nshadow, ever vigilant and protective!
It is sealed. The prince now holds pacts\nwith all surviving Greatwyrms.
Stop, Other! The Greatwyrms are with\nme now, and you will go no farther!
I suppose that DOES explain the noise.\nStill, you've come racing to your death,\nfreshly pactbound to that sorry corpse.
But no matter. Compared to the grand\nchange awaiting the world, your\nexistences are meaningless.
Impossible. I am she, and Zethia is me.\nWe are one and the same being.
And with that, a new era begins.

A new world dawns, filled with
otherworldly life, fed by the corpses
of the deceitful dragons, and watered
by the Flow Eternal.
What'n the hell is THAT thing?!\nI ain't never seen a fiend that big before!
That's a manticore! A primeval fiend!
But...we wiped them out.\nHow did this one survive?!
Oh, it didn't survive... It has returned!
Indeed! It was born anew thanks to the\npower that had long been sealed away\nin this place!
The taint here churned and thickened\nuntil I laid claim to the Auspex's body and\nset its true form free.
Such ruins are scattered across this land...\nand soon dark life will spring forth from\neach and every one!
And once the final seal is broken, a flood\nof fiends will wash over everything!\nThe Flow Eternal!
The Flow Eternal... Then you would set\nloose on these lands all the corruption\nthat lies below!
Correct! And yes, there will be some\nannoying self-styled ＂heroes＂ who rise\nup and attempt to stop it...
But I will claim this land, remake it as my\nempire, and tear those threats out by the\nthroat!
That is the true purpose of the Dyrenell\nEmpire—to defend the Flow Eternal!
In a few centuries' time, all who inhabit\nthis land will worship me utterly.
I will right this twisted world and reforge it\ninto the one it was meant to be!
You speak of righting wrongs, yet even\nnow the Empire causes innocent people\nto suffer!
Alas, this is a necessary step in correcting\na world so far distorted.
You are wrong. Stop this madness...\nNo right can come of...such suffering...
Aaah ha ha! What do you think you can do,\nbroken and powerless as you are?
But I have power enough left to send them\nfar from here!
Forgive me. My journey ends in failure;\nI was unable to avert a future of misery.
But next time... If I might be granted just\none more chance...
Etch these words into your heart, Brother,\nfor there will come a time when you\nmust decide.
Do not worry about my life.\nSeek the Dawnshard for your own.
But no matter. All is fated.
Issue a proclamation across all Grastaea...
The king is dead—long live the empress!
For all Grastaea will now bow before her\nTRUE ruler: Empress Zethia, Auspex of\nthe Nether!
